    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Styles originating in or expressing ideals supported by the post-World War I review "Zenit," which supported a strong ideology promising a brighter future, a new man, and a new society expressed in free artistic forms and Expressionism, including free verse and new typographic and graphic forms.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051960/Subotić and Vasić, 'Zenit' and Zenitism (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一次世界大戰後，由評論雜誌《澤尼特》(Zenit，意為「頂點」)所樹立或宣揚之理念所產生的風格，該雜誌大力宣揚追求更光明的未來、嶄新的人類族群以及全新的社會等意識形態，並透過不受拘束的藝術創作形式以及表現主義（Expressionism）來呈現，包括自由詩體和新的文字印刷與構圖方式。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
